Popular South African Hip-hop artist, Riky Rick has committed suicide. He was 34. Police reports said Riky Rick took his life in his home in the Northern suburbs of Johannesburg on Wednesday morning. The musician, whose real name is Rikhado Muziwendlovu Makhado, allegedly hung himself with a rope after a battle with depression. According to reports, the rapper was found in his home at 8.30 am on Wednesday by close associates and rushed to a nearby hospital but died before getting to the health facility.   What I’ll do to any woman that comes close to my ‘property’…     Lateef Adedimeji: From Ayinla to Tinubu     Twitter agog as Laycon gets GOAT emoji   Riky Rick was commonly known across the music and fashion industries in South Africa. He was famous for his iconic fashion sense and willingness to empower young artists across the country. He was the founder and owner of the Cotton Club Records label and Cotton Fest music festival. His final tweets perhaps sent a message out the world as a possible hint to his untimely death. “I’ll return a stronger man. This land is still my home,” his last tweet reads.